### Service boundary

<!-- REST-first is the template's service standard: every long-running
     component exposes FastAPI + /health + versioned /api/v1/*. The invariant is
     the boundary itself — an endpoint outside /api/v1/* or business logic reached
     without passing the app factory bypasses the one surface that is tested,
     observable, and (in split_service) authenticated. MCP is an adapter OVER this,
     never a second boundary with its own logic. -->

- paths: {{ source_root }}/**/app.py, {{ source_root }}/**/api/v1/**
- contract: Every externally reachable component is served through the FastAPI
  app factory behind versioned `/api/v1/*` with a `/health` probe; no business
  logic is exposed outside this boundary and no alternate transport (MCP,
  sidecar) carries logic of its own. Not bypassable via config or route
  registration outside the versioned prefix.
- evidence: pending — /sanyi init
{%- if frontend_backend_topology == 'split_service' %}

### Request authentication

<!-- split_service ships Supabase-JWT middleware; every API request is
